  "prompt": "What is a boy/girl called when he/she is 1-6 years old, 6-11years old, 11-14 years old, and 14-18 years old?",
  "response": "Here are the common terms used to describe the different age groups you mentioned:\n\n1. **1-6 years old**: This age group is typically referred to as **toddlers** (ages 1-3) and **preschoolers** (ages 3-6).\n\n2. **6-11 years old**: Children in this age range are commonly called **school-age children** or **preteens** (especially towards the upper end of this range, around 9-11).\n\n3. **11-14 years old**: This group is usually referred to as **preteens** or **young teenagers**. The term **tweens** is also used, particularly for those aged 11-12.\n\n4. **14-18 years old**: Individuals in this age group are called **teenagers** or **adolescents**.\n\nThese terms can vary slightly by region and cultural context, but they represent the most commonly used descriptions for these age groups.",
